                  <handDesc>
                     <p>Written along the fibers in black ink with a thick nib; it seems that the scribe was regularly dipped his pen into the inkwell; the letters are of medium-sized semi-cursive with some ligatures. The hand is slow and legible; some letters invade the interlinear space; there is a long horizontal stroke separates the text between lines 13 and 14. The verso has two lines, probably the addressee and the addressor.</p>
